The Economic Cluster ministers will unpack plans for South Africa. Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - After more than 100 days of lockdown, many businesses have shut down, and jobs lost. Ministers from the Economic Cluster delivered another briefing on Thursday. South Africa is under level 3 lockdown with some regulations tightened ahead of the peak of the COVID-19 outbreak. Government has from the start of the lockdown, been trying to balance the risk of infection and saving what was already a struggling economy.